    inLove: "Sagittarius in love is enthusiastic, generous, and genuinely exciting to be with — they will introduce you to new ideas, new places, and new ways of seeing the world. The challenge: they prize their freedom above almost everything else, and any relationship that feels confining will not last long. They need a partner who trusts them and shares their appetite for growth. Best matched with Aries and Leo (fellow fire signs who share the adventure appetite), and Libra and Aquarius who appreciate the philosophical depth.",
    atWork: "Sagittarius is the visionary who needs room to breathe. They are brilliant at the big picture, inspiring in their optimism, and capable of seeing possibilities others miss entirely. The challenge: they can lose interest once the exploration phase ends and implementation begins. Best career fits: travel writing, philosophy, higher education, law, international business, publishing, religious leadership, coaching, and any role that rewards expansive thinking.",
    mythology: "Sagittarius is associated with the centaur — specifically Chiron, the wisest and most noble of the centaurs, who was the tutor of heroes including Achilles and Jason. Unlike other centaurs (who were notoriously wild), Chiron was learned, gentle, and the source of wisdom in medicine, music, and the arts. When accidentally wounded by Heracles' poisoned arrow, Chiron chose to give up his immortality to end his suffering — a choice so noble that Zeus immortalized him in the stars. The Sagittarius archetype is this Chiron: not the savage centaur but the wise one, the teacher who has synthesized physical experience with philosophical insight. [Source: Grimal, P. (1951). The Dictionary of Classical Mythology. Blackwell.]",
