    fullDescription: "If you want to understand a Sagittarius, watch where their attention goes when they are completely free to follow it. It will go somewhere unexpected — a philosophy question, a distant country, a radical new creative idea, the one book in the bookshop nobody else picked up. Sagittarius is ruled by Jupiter, the largest planet in the solar system, and the expansion that Jupiter represents is not metaphorical — it is the sign's lived experience. More ideas, more places, more people, more meaning. The Archer symbol is perfect: always aiming at something just beyond reach, always firing toward a horizon that recedes as you approach it. Taylor Swift has rewritten her career genre several times — not because she ran out of ideas in one lane but because she ran out of room to expand in it. Bruce Lee synthesized five martial arts traditions, wrote philosophy, starred in films across three countries, and changed how the world understood Asian masculinity — all before he was 33. This is Sagittarius at full power: the restless arrow always finding a new target before the last one has cooled. The Sagittarius challenge is a real one: their love of the next thing can mean that the current thing — the relationship, the project, the commitment — gets abandoned before it matures. The arrow that never lands does not accomplish much. The evolved Sagittarius learns that depth and breadth are not opposites, and that the richest adventures are often the ones you stay in long enough to actually understand.",
